III. PROJECT RENAMING OBLIGATION

When you distribute a modified version of the Software as a standalone project,
you MUST rename the project to a name that is clearly different from the
original. This includes, but is not limited to:

- Repository name
- Binary/executable name
- Logo and visual branding

"Clearly different" means different root words and distinct visual identity -
not just changing case, punctuation, spacing, or adding numbers/suffixes.

EXCEPTIONS - You are NOT required to rename:

1. Library/Dependency usage - internal package names, class names, or
   namespaces may remain unchanged. Only the distribution name (e.g., JAR
   filename, npm package name, PyPI package name) must be renamed if
   distributed as a separate product.

2. Internal use - modifications used only within your organization.

3. Unmodified distribution - verbatim copies.

If you are unsure whether your use case requires renaming, contact the original
author for clarification.


